info.description: Registered Event Listener (rel) is a cross-platform asynchronous event dispatcher primarily designed for network applications. Select your preferred event notification methods with initialize([methods in order of preference]). If initialize(...) is not called, methods are tried in the default order: epoll, kqueue, poll, select, pyevent. Code and docs live on github: https://github.com/bubbleboy14/registeredeventlistener
info.name: rel
info.summary: Registered Event Listener. Provides standard (pyevent) interface and functionality without external dependencies
